<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4770404>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 87–89. 87. Miridiba borneensis (Moser, 1918), lectotype, ♂ (MFNB). Habitus in dorsal view. 88–89. M. coxalis (Arrow, 1944), lectotype, ♂ (BMNH). 88. Habitus in dorsal view. 89. Parameres in dorsal (A), ventral (B) and lateral (C) views. Scale bars: 87–88 = 5.0 mm; 89 = 1.0 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4770404/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4770314>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 15–17. Morphotype VI “Borneensis”. 15. Parameres of M. borneensis (Moser, 1918), lectotype (BMNH) in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views. 16. Endophallus and temones of M. coxalis (Arrow, 1944), lectotype (BMNH) in dorsal view. 17. Female genitalia of M. coxalis, paralectotype (BMNH) in dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4770314/files/figure.png" .

